long_desc.thetext:
When calling "getWidth" and "getHeight" at the "qx.ui.basic.Image" widget qooxdoo does return the values which are calculated for the widget. This might return 'null' if no explicit width and/or height is set.

I propose to add additional API for getting the width and height of the image shown by the 'qx.ui.basic.Image' widget for convenience.
Right now the developer has to do the following to get the width and height of an image.

--snip--
var myImage = new qx.ui.basic.Image("icon/22/apps/internet-web-browser.png");
this.getRoot().add(myImage);


myImage.addListener("loaded", function(e) {
  var alias = qx.util.AliasManager.getInstance().resolve("icon/22/apps/internet-web-browser.png");
  var width = qx.util.ResourceManager.getInstance().getImageWidth(alias);
  var height = qx.util.ResourceManager.getInstance().getImageHeight(alias);  
}, this);
--snip--

This is not intuitive and an API like 'getImageWidth' and 'getImageHeight' directly at the 'qx.ui.basic.Image' would be much nicer. The values are already available at the 'qx.ui.basic.Image' class.
